-- Anglo, BHP, Sasol and Telkom May Move: South African Equity Market Preview
-- B y   G a r t h   T h e u n i s s e n
-- 2010-10-11T04:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-10/anglo-bhp-sasol-telkom-south-african-equity-market-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in  South Africa .
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.  South Africa’s  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index  rose 123.88,
or 0.4 percent, to 29,647.99 at the close in Johannesburg.  Anglo American Plc  (AGL SJ): Copper prices rose to a 27-
month high, rallying as much as 3.1 percent to $8,349.50 a
metric ton on the London Metal Exchange. Stock of Anglo, the
diversified mining company that makes up almost 10 percent of
South Africa’s benchmark stock index, rose 6.40 rand, or 2.2
percent, to 298.50 rand. Shares in larger rival  BHP Billiton Plc 
(BIL SJ) gained 3.20 rand, or 1.4 percent, to 236.10 rand.  Sasol Ltd.  (SOL SJ): Oil climbed as much as 1.8 percent to
$83.13 a barrel. Stock of Sasol, the world’s biggest maker of
motor fuel from coal, fell 4.35 rand, or 1.3 percent, to 320.25
rand.  Telkom South Africa Ltd.  (TKG SJ): Officials from Africa’s
largest fixed-line phone operator will appear before antitrust
authorities today to argue for the dismissal of cases brought
against the company by the Competition Commission and Internet
Solutions. The company’s stock was unchanged at 37 rand.  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) added 3.1 percent to $21.70.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) rose 1.1 percent to $46.99. BHP
Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) rose 2.3 percent to $68.95. DRDGold Ltd.
(DROOY US) fell 1.1 percent to $5.21. Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI US)
added 1 percent to $15.67. Harmony Gold Mining Co. (HMY US)
climbed 0.6 percent to $11.48. Impala Platinum Holdings Co.
(IMPUY US) gained 1.8 percent to $28.15. Sappi Ltd. (SPP US)
lost 1.8 percent to $5.04. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) gained 0.5
percent to $47.37 Telkom South Africa Ltd. (TLKGY US) advanced
0.3 percent to $21.45.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Garth Theunissen  in Johannesburg 
